This paper is about speech recognition using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) and their limitations, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper focuses on the development of small-footprint models, which could fall under the sub-category of system and control (cs.SD).
